Hi, 

the goal is to thicken a flame artificially. For a premixed flame, if you divide reaction rates by a factor F and multiply diffusion by F, you will obtain a F times larger flame but with the same flame velocity ( Poinsot & Veynante, Theoretical and numerical combustion for details). It is very usefull on LES to compute a flame when the mesh size isn&#39;t large enough compared to the flame size.

I did it with the premixed flame and will try to test it on  diffusion flames. Thanks for all your help.

Happy new year,

Guillaume

